<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="308" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,937,1615]" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,1050,1075]" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">Description.</emphasis>
Head and thorax pale testaceous with brown speckling. Vertex with darker markings anterior along shallow transverse depression. Tegmen mottled in patches with brown, darker apically, with line of brown spots inside costal margin. Posterior brown marking well defined anteriorly, less so posteriorly. Ventrally, abdomen pale, female terminalia brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,937,1615]" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">Male genitalia. Subgenital plates broadly rounded at base, then margins lightly curved before abruptly narrowing to elongate posterior fingerlike process. Paramere with posterior process long, tapering, divergent from opposing paramere process. Connective with arms longer than stem. Aedeagus with shafts moderately divergent in posterior view, curved dorsally to be almost parallel towards apex, with narrow elongate basal process from posterior edge of each shaft extending to about half length of shafts. In lateral view, shafts more or less straight to almost midlength then curved anteriorly to reveal apex of basal process, slightly tapering from base to apex where apical process is hooked anteriorly.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="308" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,937,1615]" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1446,1471]" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">Comments.</emphasis>
This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Knight" box="[695,868,1447,1471]" pageId="7" pageNumber="308" refString="Knight, W. J. (1970 a) A revision of the genus Hishimonus Ishihara (Hom., Cicadellidae). Suomen Hyonteistieteellinen Aikakauskirja, 36 (3), 125 - 139" type="journal article" year="1970" yearSuffix="a">
Knight (
<number box="[789,847,1447,1471]" pageId="7" pageNumber="308" value="1970.0">1970</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
based on a single male specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[1321,1407,1447,1471]" name="Taiwan" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. It shows affinity with 
<taxonomicName box="[374,516,1483,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diffractus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[374,516,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">H. diffractus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[524,614,1483,1507]" pageId="7" pageNumber="308" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[524,614,1483,1507]" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in which the basal processes are united with the shaft of the aedeagus on each side rather than being separate from the shaft throughout their length as in this species. Both species have the subgenital plates abruptly narrowed apically before the apical fingerlike process, a feature they also share with 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gillespiei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">H. gillespiei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[308,449,1591,1615]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diffractus">
<emphasis box="[308,449,1591,1615]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">H. diffractus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
